commit.message:
In Pandoc and CslJson CaseTransform, group punctuation in clusters.

This should fix #127.

Fix sorting on dates.

Previously this broke for some styles, e.g. apa.csl, which styles
dates as MM/DD/YYYY, and would lead to incorrect sorting of dates
with months and/or days.  With this change we sort on a normalized
date YYYY-MM-DD (though using only the components that would be
rendered), as described in the spec.

(As a trick to handle proper sorting of positive and negative dates,
we add 5000 internally when sorting the year.)

Closes #126.

Add citation-key variable from citeId.

This is a new addition in CSL 1.0.2.
Raise an error if multiple layout elements are present (#120).

Fix two test cases.

They had illegal bibliography elements with no layout children.

If there are multiple layout elements, only use the last one.

This can happen with CSL-M styles. The last layout should be locale-unspecific.

This change will prevent us from emitting doubled citations or
bibliographic references (see #120), allowing more graceful handling
of CSL-M styles, even though we don't support CSL-M.

Previously we simply concatenated the elements of all the layout
elements.
CI: trim out older ghc versions and macos bulids.

Fix disappearing locator after collapsed year suffix.

Closes #96.

Fix disambiguation edge case.

We weren't properly disambiguating when only one of two
ambiguous names had a subsequent citation.

This also fixes two additional tests we were not passing
previously!

Closes #116.

Require data-default >= 0.5.2 (#114)

Otherwise build fails with
```
$ cabal build --constraint 'data-default == 0.5.1'
src/Citeproc/Locale.hs:29:20: error:
    • No instance for (Data.Default.Default X.ParseSettings)
        arising from a use of ‘def’
    • In the first argument of ‘X.parseText’, namely ‘def’
      In the first argument of ‘($)’, namely ‘X.parseText def’
      In the expression: X.parseText def $ TL.fromStrict t
   |
29 |   case X.parseText def $ TL.fromStrict t of
   |                    ^^^
```

commit.message: CI: use ghcup to install ghc, etc.

Don't increment count of used variables for SubstitutedVal.

Previously groups with subsituted variables would sometimes be included.

Closes #108.

Fix logic for including a group.

A group with a text node and an empty variable should
count as empty.
